tellraw @s {"text":"\n-------------- Rauchergames Setup Guide --------------","color":"green"}
tellraw @s {"text":"\nLong Version:","color":"green"}
tellraw @s [{"text":"Overwiew: ","color":"light_purple"},{"text":"Wokkagames (don't ask about the name) consists of multiple pvp game modes (plus one for testing), that are all played with up to 12 players divided into 2 teams (while it is possible to play alone, at least 2 players per team are recommended). Each player can choose from one of several kits with unique stats and abilities.","color":"yellow"}]
tellraw @s [{"text":"\nResource Pack: ","color":"light_purple"},{"text":"Make sure you have the ","color":"yellow"},{"text":"Wokka Resource Pack ","color":"gold","hover_event":{"action":"show_text","value":[{"text":"Click to open link to Resource Pack"}]},"click_event":{"action":"open_url","url":"https://github.com/flaviusmus/rauch_texturepack"}},{"text":"intalled.","color":"yellow"}]
tellraw @s [{"text":"\nAdmins: ","color":"light_purple"},{"text":"To edit game settings, start games, add/remove maps etc. you need to be an admin. You can become an admin using the command (","color":"yellow"},{"text":"/tag NAME add admin","hover_event":{"action":"show_text","value":[{"text":"Click to Suggest Command"}]},"click_event":{"action":"suggest_command","command":"/tag NAME add admin"},"color":"gold"},{"text":"). You can do this with every player you want, however they also need rights on the server (permission level 2 or more). To remove admin rights, do (","color":"yellow"},{"text":"/tag NAME remove admin","hover_event":{"action":"show_text","value":[{"text":"Click to Suggest Command"}]},"click_event":{"action":"suggest_command","command":"/tag REPLACE_WITH_NAME remove admin"},"color":"gold"},{"text":"). Admins have access to the \"Settings\" Book in their first hotbar slot. From here you can change game modes, maps and more.","color":"yellow"}]
tellraw @s [{"text":"\nLobby: ","color":"light_purple"},{"text":"The lobby is the place players return to after a game. You can spawn it using the \"Edit Lobby Settings\" option found on the 3rd page of the Settings book. You can define your own lobby position there as well if you prefer that.","color":"yellow"}]
tellraw @s [{"text":"\nAdding a Map: ","color":"light_purple"},{"text":"At least one map must exist to play on. Go to the 2nd page of the \"Settings\" book and click on \"Add Map\". Here you can decide between spawning a prebuilt map, or adding a custom map.","color":"yellow"}]
tellraw @s [{"text":"\nKits: ","color":"light_purple"},{"text":"Before starting, each player has to select a kit using the book called \"Kit Selector / Settings\". You can see their stats and abilities by hovering over the name. Click to select. Each class has three abilities, R, Q and F. In game, you can activate R by right-clicking and Q and F by pressing the respective key on your keyboard. Some abilities require you to crouch while using them (shift-F or sF etc.). The \"Wokkaman\" kit can not be selected by default as it is kind of a boss kit for the Wokkaman mode.","color":"yellow"}]
tellraw @s [{"text":"\nGame Modes: ","color":"light_purple"},{"text":"Admins can choose a game mode using the \"Settings\" Book. Hovering over the name will show information about the mode.","color":"yellow"}]
tellraw @s [{"text":"\nStarting a Game: ","color":"light_purple"},{"text":"After having selected a kit and a map (using the 2nd page of the \"Settings\" Book), right click with the green item called \"Join Queue\" to join the queue. Here all players can choose a team (players that don't pick will be evenly distributed). Note that there is nothing (except evil admins and/or your friendship) preventing unbalanced teams (like a 3v1).","color":"yellow"}]
tellraw @s [{"text":"\nUtility Functions (feat. Aborting Games): ","color":"light_purple"},{"text":"Players with rights on the server can use helpful utility functions, just type ","color":"yellow"},{"text":"/function utils_rauch","hover_event":{"action":"show_text","value":[{"text":"Click to Suggest Command"}]},"click_event":{"action":"suggest_command","command":"/function utils_rauch:"},"color":"gold"},{"text":" and the functions should be available via auto-complete. The names of the functions should be self-explanatory.","color":"yellow"}]
tellraw @s {"text":"\nShort Version:","color":"green"}
tellraw @s [{"text":"1. ",color:"light_purple"},{text:"Make sure you have the Resource Pack installed","color":"yellow"},{"text":" (link)","color":"gold","hover_event":{"action":"show_text","value":[{"text":"Click to open link to Resource Pack"}]},"click_event":{"action":"open_url","url":"https://github.com/flaviusmus/rauch_texturepack"}}]
tellraw @s [{"text":"2. ",color:"light_purple"},{text:"Type ","color":"yellow"},{"text":"/tag @s add admin","color":"gold","hover_event":{"action":"show_text","value":[{"text":"Click to Suggest Command"}]},"click_event":{"action":"suggest_command","command":"/tag @s add admin"}},{"text":" to become an admin to get the \"Settings\" book.","color":"yellow"}]
tellraw @s [{"text":"3. ",color:"light_purple"},{text:"Spawn Lobby (\"Lobby Settings\" Option on the 3rd page of \"Settings\" book)","color":"yellow"}]
tellraw @s [{"text":"4. ",color:"light_purple"},{text:"Spawn a prebuilt map (\"Add Map\" on 2nd page of \"Settings\" Book)","color":"yellow"}]
tellraw @s [{"text":"5. ",color:"light_purple"},{text:"Select a map (2nd page of \"Settings\" Book)","color":"yellow"}]
tellraw @s [{"text":"6. ",color:"light_purple"},{text:"Select a game mode (1st page of \"Settings\" Book)","color":"yellow"}]
tellraw @s [{"text":"7. ",color:"light_purple"},{text:"Everyone has to select a kit and join the queue","color":"yellow"}]
tellraw @s [{"text":"8. ",color:"light_purple"},{text:"An admin has to start the game","color":"yellow"}]
tellraw @s {"text":"------------------- Setup Guide End -------------------","color":"green"}
